{"word":"ἐπαξιόω","slug":"ἐπαξιόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπαξιόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἐπάξιος'><el>ἐπάξιος</el></a>\n<el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ώσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to think right, deem right</i> to do a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to expect, believe</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>ἐπ. τινά</el> <i>to deem</i> one <i>worthy of honour</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}